name: Antonio MARTINEZ, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY FIRST JUDICIAL DISTRICT PENNSYLVANIA, Respondent
name_abbreviation: Martinez v. Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia County First Judicial District Pennsylvania

parties: Antonio MARTINEZ, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY FIRST JUDICIAL DISTRICT PENNSYLVANIA, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 16th day of December, 2009, the Application for Leave to File Original Process and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief are GRANTED. The Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia is directed to dispose of the Post Conviction Relief Act petition filed by Petitioner on May 16, 2008 within 90 days of this order. See CP-51-CR-0530631-1989.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.
